      <prefercite id="aspace_2559cb2626e6a2cf9b4edf63b6fdcdee">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Lyman Hotchkiss Bagg Papers (MS 849). Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.</p>
      </prefercite>
      <bioghist id="aspace_aea3d1d6c16bfd75cf78d8e784815e8e">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Lyman Hotchkiss Bagg: author, journalist; editor of <title render="italic">
               <part>Yale Literary Magazine</part>
            </title>, 1868-1869, and of the <title render="italic">
               <part>College Courant</part>
            </title> (New Haven), 1870-1871; wrote weekly "College Chronicle" for the <title render="italic">
               <part>New York World</part>
            </title>, 1876-1882; author of numerous books.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_5a48626823d58177fceafb610b92c4aa">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>Correspondence, manuscripts, and other papers largely relating to Lyman Hotchkiss Bagg's interest in boating; his editorship of the <title render="italic">
               <part>Yale Literary Magazine</part>
            </title>, 1868-1869; and his weekly "College Chronicle" written for the <title render="italic">
               <part>New York World</part>
            </title>, 1876-1882. Also included are student translations from Latin and Greek, and correspondence and memorabilia from his years at Yale College, 1865-1869.</p>
      </scopecontent>
